### Summary / Problem Statement
The redaction registry (\`secret-redaction-registry.ts\`) prevents credential leaks by replacing registered values in logs. To limit memory usage, it caps the registry at 512 entries using FIFO eviction:
```typescript
if (registeredValues.size > MAX_SECRET_VALUES) {
  const oldest = registeredValues.keys().next().value;
  if (oldest !== undefined) {
    registeredValues.delete(oldest);
  }
}
```
